import java.util.HashMap;

public int numSubarraysWithSum(int[] nums, int goal) {
    HashMap<Integer, Integer> prefixSumCount = new HashMap<>();
    prefixSumCount.put(0, 1);
    int sum = 0, result = 0;

    for (int num : nums) {
        sum += num;
        result += prefixSumCount.getOrDefault(sum - goal, 0);
        prefixSumCount.put(sum, prefixSumCount.getOrDefault(sum, 0) + 1);
    }

    return result;
}
```

    The algorithm uses the prefix sum technique with a hash map to store the count of each prefix sum. It iterates through the given binary array, adding each element to the cumulative sum. For each cumulative sum, the algorithm checks how many prefix sums are equal to the current cumulative sum minus the given goal. The algorithm then adds this count to the result.

After iterating through the entire array, the result will be the number of non-empty subarrays with a sum equal to the given goal.
